text: <@UCY83QS6Q>  <@UAYBXDG4U> you are much smarter guys than I am, so I’m confident that you can fix this.

Yep, that’s the best thing with these new jsx-fields is, that you know what data is coming to your components from the fields and you see the model! Previously I was using in the old customized HS React framework HubSpot js fields, but that was written in `commonjs`, so even thought I had an own npm library for the fields (ts) and used those in the old HS React framework (ts), I still needed to export those from `commonjs` and by doing that losing the types.
